Wilfred Laurier (sorry, my bad) University of Waterloo is the latest school to fall victim to these self-proclaimed activists. Christie Blatchford was set to give a talk to a small but enthusiastic crowd of people about her new book, Helpless: Caledonia&#8217;s Nightmare of Fear [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Free speech <a href="http://takebackyourschool.wordpress.com/2010/11/14/christie-blatchford/">has apparently ceased to exist</a> at the University of Waterloo:<br />
<blockquote><i>Wilfred Laurier (sorry, my bad) University of Waterloo is the latest school to fall victim to these self-proclaimed activists. Christie Blatchford was set to give a talk to a small but enthusiastic crowd of people about her new book, Helpless: Caledonia&#8217;s Nightmare of Fear and Anarchy, and How the Law Failed All of Us. </i>
<p><i>[...] They stormed in, put up a huge sign with a swastika on stage, locked arms, and refused to leave. They yelled and screamed at the audience and accused them all of being racists who weren&#8217;t welcome on &#8220;their&#8221; campus. When one man tried to ask them exactly what they wanted, the heavy-set female in filthy jeans exclaimed that she would not engage in discussion with &#8220;Nazis&#8221;. </i></p>
</blockquote>
<p align="left">My alma mater. As you can imagine, I am soooo proud.</p>
<p>Unfortunately, it seems that Canada is fast becoming a country where free speech no longer exists, and only the &quot;right&quot; opinions are tolerated by those who know what is good for the rest of us. I remember when I started reading Ayn Rand novels and my parents told me that Canada would never be like that. Apparently things change.</p>
<p align="left">Tip of the hat to <a href="http://www.smalldeadanimals.com/archives/015337.html">small dead animals</a>.</p>
